  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Projet d&#x2019;am&#xE9;lioration des conditions de vie des populations affect&#xE9;es par la crise centrafricaine au Sud du Tchad</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this joint project between FAO, UNFPA, UNHCR, UNICEF and WFP is to provide basic humanitarian needs (food security, protection, shelter, sanitation and water) for the population affected by the RCA crisis in Logone Oriental and Moyen Chari. UN agencies will use CERF funds to provide multipurpose cash assistance and protection services, among other activities. 41,393 refugees and returnees will benefit from this project, which will be implemented within 9 months.</narrative>
  </description>
